{
  "doc_id": "27552",
  "text": "A conventional three-electrode system was employed with a modified glassy carbon electrode (GCE, 3.0 mm in diameter) as the working electrode, a platinum electrode as the counter electrode, and an Ag/AgCl electrode with saturated KCl as the reference electrode [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . All potentials reported in this article were referenced to the Ag/AgCl electrode. Hexacyanoferrate (K 3 [Fe(CN) 6 ]) is chosen as the redox probe of the INS/NINS sensors in solutions because TBP is electroinactive over the studied potential range. All measurements were carried out at room temperature.",
